DataElement.preferredDefinition: The structural organization of a gene in DNA.  Refers to the arrangement of elements that comprise a gene or transcription unit, among which are the transcription initiation site, the protein coding sequences, intervening sequences, and the transcription termination or polyadenylation sites.  Also includes the regulatory elements (enhancers, silencers, and the promoter) that lie outside the boundaries of the transcribed unit.:An explanatory or critical comment that has been added to a text.:A position, site, or point in space where something can be found._Indicates the direction and/or type of the SeqFeature, i.e. whether it is in the 5' or 3' direction, is double stranded, etc._Value Domain for java language String datatype.
